6:
Completely out of the question! 
What do you take the champion for?!
10:
Ooh, someone's a little touchy. 
Wouldn't you agree, Aperio?
19: Oh? What brings you two here?
23:
I thought I just saw Light bolt outta 
here with a disturbed look on his 
face...
28:
Hehe. I wonder what could've possibly 
gotten into him?
33: I can think of a few things...
36: So, what do I owe this pleasure to?
40: We're here to see Aperio, actually.
48:
Correct. He assisted me with my 
shopping duties the other day.
50:
I've brought him some meat today 
as a reward for his efforts.
64:
Oh, no, it's okay! You're free to act as 
you please, darling.
73:
Why, of course! I'm his master, 
after all.
75:
We've been together ever since the 
day I first cracked open this grimoire. 
It's only natural we'd understand each 
other.
92:
Perhaps I brought him a little too 
much.
96:
I mean, he may be a dragon, but he's 
still just a kid, right?
98:
Wait... Does this mean he'll grow into 
a dragon-sized dragon someday?
102:
I'm... not sure, to be honest. He's been 
the same size since the day we first 
met.
104:
He can't fly for very long, either—
although he SHOULD be able to, all 
things considered.
111:
Aww, I'm sorry, Aperio. I wasn't trying 
to be mean.
116: You really must love him, don't you?
122: Wh-what are you saying all of a sudden?
125:
When making something your pet, 
is that your way of showing your love 
for them?
130:
N-no! It's nothing so basic as that! 
It's much more, uh...
133:
It seems I was mistaken. 
So you don't love Aperio then.
136: That's not what I meant by—Ugh!
141:
I think you two have overstayed your 
welcome!
153:
*sigh* Just how red is my face right 
now, Aperio?
